import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median Age: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the age distribution of the deceased individuals?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Age")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(gender_counts.index, title="Gender", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
